    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Manifolds and Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR) - Cleaning, Inspection and Test
        - Intake Manifold
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Intake Manifold</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean machined surfaces of intake manifold and mating surfaces of cylinder heads.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bolt intake manifold onto cylinder heads without gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten bolts using the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_69.xml" xrefid="f3000422">intake manifold torque sequence</hotlnk>
                and to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_73.xml" xrefid="E30004B" appearance="hottext">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check each port by trying to pass a 0.003 in Feeler Gauge between the intake manifold and
                cylinder head. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_74.xml" xrefid="E30004C" appearance="hottext">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If specifications for intake manifold cannot be met, replace intake manifold. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_72.xml" xrefid="E30004A">Specifications</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If it was determined to install a new intake manifold, any remaining intake manifold testing
                steps will not be necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove intake manifold.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000413" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ14/J14017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Test plates installed on intake manifold</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install Intake Manifold Pressure Test Plates. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_74.xml" xrefid="E30004C" appearance="hottext">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000414" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ14/J14018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Intake manifold pressure test</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR valve plug</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Test plates</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Intake manifold pressure test cap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air supply pressure regulator</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install Intake Manifold Pressure Test Plug in EGR valve opening. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_74.xml" xrefid="E30004C" appearance="hottext">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install Intake Manifold Pressure Test Cap onto air intake. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_74.xml" xrefid="E30004C" appearance="hottext">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, wear safety glasses with side shields when
                    using compressed air for cleaning to reduce the danger from flying debris. Limit the air pressure to
                    207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Submerge the intake manifold assembly in water. Pressurize to 172 to 207 kPa (25 to 30 psi)
                using a regulated filtered air supply. Inspect for leaks in the intake plenum, EGR and coolant passages.
                Replace if necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect intake manifold gasket seal beads for defects. Replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
